Jeanette Chabalala, News24 (File, iStock) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Cape Town &ndash; The city of Cape Town announced that level two water restrictions will be implemented from January 1. &nbsp;The city said in a statement that the restrictions are set to save 20% of the city&rsquo;s daily water usage.&ldquo;With level 2 restrictions approved, residents will be charged according to 20% reduction tariffs to discourage greater water-use efficiency.&rdquo; &nbsp; The public will only be able to wash vehicles with hosepipes fitted with an automatic self-closing device. &nbsp;Residents are also encouraged to replace all taps, shower heads and other plumbing components with water efficient parts or technologies. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.